In this proclamation, President Donald J. Trump declares June 2020 as Great Outdoors Month in the United States. The proclamation highlights the natural beauty of the country and the importance of outdoor spaces for recreation and renewal. The administration is committed to restoring and preserving land, air, and water, as well as increasing recreational opportunities for all Americans. Actions such as expanding access to public lands and joining the One Trillion Trees Initiative demonstrate a commitment to conservation and responsible stewardship of the environment. The proclamation encourages Americans to explore the great outdoors while acting as stewards of the land and water.